<html><h1 style="margin-top:16px"><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2e74b5"><span style="font-weight:normal">View metrics collected using MP for MP for IBM WebSphere Application Server (2018.11) as reports on BVD</span></span></span></span></span></h1>

<h1 style="margin-top:16px"><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2e74b5"><span style="font-weight:normal">Prerequisites</span></span></span></span></span></h1>

<ul>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">OpsB Suite 2020.08 should be installed</span></span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">OBM 2020.05 should be installed.</span></span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">Certificate exchange between the OBM and COSO Data Lake should be done. For more information, see </span><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/Operations_Bridge:2019.11/ConfigureCOSODataLake" style="color:blue; text-decoration:underline">https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/Operations_Bridge:2019.11/ConfigureCOSODataLake</a>.</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">BVD should be connected to COSO Data Lake.</span></span></span></span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

<h1 style="margin-top:16px"><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2e74b5"><span style="font-weight:normal">Task 1: Install MP for IBM WebSphere Application Server on OBM</span></span></span></span></span></h1>
<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></span></span><br>
<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="vertical-align:middle"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">Follow the steps mentioned on the </span><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/MP_for_IBM_WebSphere_Application_Server:2018.11/Content_IG/Common/Installing_MP_on_BSM_Server" style="color:blue; text-decoration:underline">Install MP for IBM WebSphere Application Server</a><span style="color:black"> page.</span></span></span></span></span>

<h1 style="margin-top:16px"><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2e74b5"><span style="font-weight:normal">Task 2: Install OA on the WebSphere server which you want to monitor.</span></span></span></span></span></h1>
<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">For more information on different methods of installing OA, see </span></span><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/Operations_Agent:12.14/InstallationMethods" style="color:blue; text-decoration:underline"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Installation methods</span></span></a><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">.</span></span></span></span></span></span>

<h1 style="margin-top:16px"><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2e74b5"><span style="font-weight:normal">Task 3: Perform certificate exchange between OA and OBM.</span></span></span></span></span></h1>
<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">For more information, see <a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/Operations_Agent:12.14/ConnectingOBM" style="color:blue; text-decoration:underline">https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/Operations_Agent:12.14/ConnectingOBM</a>.</span></span></span>

<h1 style="margin-top:16px"><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2e74b5"><span style="font-weight:normal">Task 5: Run scripts to create tables in COSO Data Lake.</span></span></span></span></span></h1>
<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></span></span>

<ol>
	<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="tab-stops:list .5in"><span style="vertical-align:middle"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="color:#212529">Run the following command to get the Operations Bridge namespace:&nbsp;<br>
	kubectl get ns</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
	<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="tab-stops:list .5in"><span style="vertical-align:middle"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="color:#212529">Run the following command to get the list all the pods that are a part of the Operations Bridge namespace:&nbsp;<br>
	kubectl get pods -n &lt;Operations Bridge namespace&gt;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
	<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="tab-stops:list .5in"><span style="vertical-align:middle"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="color:#212529">Copy the Operations Bridge Content Administration pod (itom-opsb-content-administration-&lt;pod ID&gt;) name and then run the command to log on:<br>
	kubectl -n &lt;Operations Bridge namespace&gt; exec -ti &lt;Operations Bridge Content Administration pod&gt; -c itom-opsb-content-administration bash</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
	<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="tab-stops:list .5in"><span style="vertical-align:middle"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="color:#212529">Run the following commands to install&nbsp;<i>SQL </i>content:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:black">opsb-content-service.sh easyconfigure -configuration_types metadata -category <span style="background:yellow">webspheremp</span>.</span></span></span></span></span><br>
<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></span></span><br>
<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="color:#212529">After you have performed the above steps, all the related tables are created in the COSO Data Lake.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br>
<br>
<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></span></span>

<h1 style="margin-top:16px"><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="color:#2e74b5"><span style="font-weight:normal">Task 6: Deploy WebSphere Metric Store aspect.</span></span></span></span></span></h1>
<br>
<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="letter-spacing:.15pt">Follow the steps to deploy the WebSphere Metrics Store aspect:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>

<ol>
	<li style="margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="tab-stops:list .5in"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Click&nbsp;<b>Administration &gt; Monitoring &gt; Management Templates &amp; Aspects</b>.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="tab-stops:list .5in"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">In the&nbsp;<b>Configuration Folders</b>&nbsp;pane, expand Application Server management &gt; IBM WebSphere Management.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="tab-stops:list .5in"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">In the&nbsp;<b>Management Templates &amp; Aspects</b>&nbsp;pane, select the WebSphere Metric&nbsp;<b>Store</b>&nbsp;aspect, and then click&nbsp;<b>Assign and Deploy</b>&nbsp;Item. The Assign and Deploy wizard opens.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="tab-stops:list .5in"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">In the&nbsp;<b>Configuration Item</b>&nbsp;tab, select the managed node (where the WebSphere server is running) to deploy the WebSphere Metric Store aspect, and then click&nbsp;<b>Next</b>. The&nbsp;<b>Required Parameters</b>&nbsp;tab opens.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="tab-stops:list .5in"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">In the&nbsp;<b>Required Parameters</b>&nbsp;tab, select the&nbsp;<b>Target Server</b>&nbsp;parameter, and click&nbsp;<b>Edit</b>. The Edit Parameter window appears. Select&nbsp;<b>Value</b>, enter the value, and then click&nbsp;<b>OK</b>.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="tab-stops:list .5in"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Click&nbsp;<b>Next</b>. The&nbsp;<b>Parameters Summary</b>&nbsp;tab opens.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="tab-stops:list .5in"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">In the&nbsp;<b>Parameter Summary</b>&nbsp;tab, select the&nbsp;<b>WebSphere</b>&nbsp;<b>Metric Store Frequency</b>&nbsp;parameter, and click&nbsp;<b>Edit</b>&nbsp;to change the default value of five minutes. The&nbsp;<b>Edit Parameter</b>&nbsp;Window appears. Select&nbsp;<b>Value</b>, enter the value, and then click&nbsp;<b>OK</b>. You can enter only the values [null 5, 15, 30, and 60]</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="tab-stops:list .5in"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Click&nbsp;<b>Next</b>. The&nbsp;<b>Configure Options</b>&nbsp;tab opens.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="tab-stops:list .5in"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">In the&nbsp;<b>Configure Options</b>&nbsp;tab, the&nbsp;<b>Enable Assignment(s)</b>&nbsp;check box is selected by default. Click&nbsp;<b>Finish</b>.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
</ol>
<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif"><span style="letter-spacing:.15pt">After you deploy the WebSphere Metric Store aspect, the following message appears:&nbsp;<i>Assignment and deployment jobs created.</i></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>

